cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY 

This paper deals with pedestrian motion prediction using machine learning techniques. The use of motion primitives and Gaussian Processes for modeling transitions suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The incremental learning aspect of the algorithm also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO), as these fields often deal with learning from data and adapting to new situations. Finally, the testing and evaluation of the algorithm in intersection scenarios suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
